<Algorithm code="             1. If _n_ is *NaN* or _d_ is *NaN*, return *NaN*.             1. If _n_ is either *+∞*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt; or *-∞*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt;, return *NaN*.             1. If _d_ is either *+∞*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt; or *-∞*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt;, return _n_.             1. If _d_ is either *+0*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt; or *-0*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt;, return *NaN*.             1. If _n_ is either *+0*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt; or *-0*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt;, return _n_.             1. Assert: _n_ and _d_ are finite and non-zero.             1. Let _quotient_ be ℝ(_n_) / ℝ(_d_).             1. Let _q_ be truncate(_quotient_).             1. Let _r_ be ℝ(_n_) - (ℝ(_d_) × _q_).             1. If _r_ = 0 and _n_ &lt; *-0*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt;, return *-0*&lt;sub&gt;𝔽&lt;/sub&gt;.             1. Return 𝔽(_r_).           ">
